children.subject: If I got an A on stat 134, will EECS 126 be considered low difficulty, medium workload for me?
i wouldnt take eecs126 if youve already taken stat134+stat140
I did not take Stat 140, I just took Stat 134. I heard from lots of people that EECS 126 covers a lot more concepts than Stat 134?

CS 189: medium-high difficulty, high workload

EECS 127: medium difficulty, medium workload

(127 and 189 are somewhat similar in material and difficulty. If you take 189 in fall/not with Shewchuk it'll probably be more work/hw and more theoretical.)

EECS 126: medium difficulty, medium workload

(even though I'd say 126 and 127 are similar in terms of these metrics, they're very different styles in that 126 covers a lot of small topics while 127 focuses on a few key concepts in depth so this may affect your perception of difficulty)

Don't know too much about 100 but it should be on the lighter side compared to these.

history.content:
can you provide your opinion on the difficulty and workload of CS 189, EECS 127, EECS 126, Data 100 comparing to CS 170, CS 188, and lower-division courses?

I think,

CS 170 is high difficulty, medium workload,

CS 61ABC is medium difficulty, high workload,

Stat 134/Math 104/Math 113/Math 185 is medium difficulty, low workload,

CS 188/CS 70/Math 110 is low difficulty, low workload.

What would you think of CS 189, EECS 127, EECS 126, Data 100 for me? (I have not taken EECS 16B, but I am very familiar with PCA & SVD)
